{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1008,"text":"When people think about cities,"},{"time":2698,"text":"they tend to think of certain things."},{"time":5000,"text":"They think of buildings and streets"},{"time":7060,"text":"and skyscrapers, noisy cabs."},{"time":9956,"text":"But when I think about cities,"},{"time":11890,"text":"I think about people."},{"time":13691,"text":"Cities are fundamentally about people,"},{"time":17161,"text":"and where people go"},{"time":19005,"text":"and where people meet"},{"time":20520,"text":"are at the core of what makes a city work."},{"time":23850,"text":"So even more important than buildings in a city"},{"time":27030,"text":"are the public spaces in between them."},{"time":30038,"text":"And today, some of the most transformative"},{"time":32696,"text":"changes in cities"},{"time":34373,"text":"are happening in these public spaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37559,"text":"So I believe that lively, enjoyable public spaces"},{"time":41752,"text":"are the key to planning a great city."},{"time":44872,"text":"They are what makes it come alive."},{"time":48292,"text":"But what makes a public space work?"},{"time":51972,"text":"What attracts people to successful public spaces,"},{"time":55523,"text":"and what is it about unsuccessful places"},{"time":57945,"text":"that keeps people away?"},{"time":60625,"text":"I thought, if I could answer those questions,"},{"time":63984,"text":"I could make a huge contribution to my city."},{"time":67764,"text":"But one of the more wonky things about me"},{"time":69918,"text":"is that I am an animal behaviorist,"},{"time":73469,"text":"and I use those skills not to study animal behavior"},{"time":77046,"text":"but to study how people in cities"},{"time":79980,"text":"use city public spaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82228,"text":"One of the first spaces that I studied"},{"time":85549,"text":"was this little vest pocket park called Paley Park"},{"time":88954,"text":"in midtown Manhattan."},{"time":91262,"text":"This little space became a small phenomenon,"},{"time":95387,"text":"and because it had such a profound impact"},{"time":98255,"text":"on New Yorkers,"},{"time":99471,"text":"it made an enormous impression on me."},{"time":103555,"text":"I studied this park very early on in my career"},{"time":106052,"text":"because it happened to have been built"},{"time":107638,"text":"by my stepfather,"},{"time":109416,"text":"so I knew that places like Paley Park"},{"time":112048,"text":"didn't happen by accident."},{"time":114448,"text":"I saw firsthand that they required"},{"time":117000,"text":"incredible dedication"},{"time":118456,"text":"and enormous attention to detail."},{"time":121514,"text":"But what was it about this space"},{"time":123248,"text":"that made it special and drew people to it?"},{"time":127050,"text":"Well, I would sit in the park and watch very carefully,"},{"time":129951,"text":"and first among other things"},{"time":131843,"text":"were the comfortable, movable chairs."},{"time":134906,"text":"People would come in, find their own seat,"},{"time":137416,"text":"move it a bit, actually, and then stay a while,"},{"time":140810,"text":"and then interestingly,"},{"time":142658,"text":"people themselves attracted other people,"},{"time":145633,"text":"and ironically, I felt more peaceful"},{"time":148410,"text":"if there were other people around."},{"time":150391,"text":"And it was green."},{"time":152281,"text":"This little park provided what New Yorkers crave:"},{"time":156042,"text":"comfort and greenery."},{"time":158580,"text":"But my question was,"},{"time":160268,"text":"why weren't there more places with greenery"},{"time":163330,"text":"and places to sit in the middle of the city"},{"time":165839,"text":"where you didn't feel alone,"},{"time":168319,"text":"or like a trespasser?"},{"time":170776,"text":"Unfortunately, that's not how cities"},{"time":173008,"text":"were being designed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175026,"text":"So here you see a familiar sight."},{"time":178720,"text":"This is how plazas have been\ndesigned for generations."},{"time":183001,"text":"They have that stylish, Spartan look"},{"time":186131,"text":"that we often associate with modern architecture,"},{"time":189951,"text":"but it's not surprising that people"},{"time":192262,"text":"avoid spaces like this."},{"time":194124,"text":"They not only look desolate,"},{"time":196234,"text":"they feel downright dangerous."},{"time":198946,"text":"I mean, where would you sit here?"},{"time":202223,"text":"What would you do here?"},{"time":204769,"text":"But architects love them."},{"time":208245,"text":"They are plinths for their creations."},{"time":211518,"text":"They might tolerate a sculpture or two,"},{"time":213451,"text":"but that's about it."},{"time":215204,"text":"And for developers, they are ideal."},{"time":218408,"text":"There's nothing to water, nothing to maintain,"},{"time":220995,"text":"and no undesirable people to worry about."},{"time":224955,"text":"But don't you think this is a waste?"},{"time":228199,"text":"For me, becoming a city planner"},{"time":230520,"text":"meant being able to truly change the city"},{"time":233192,"text":"that I lived in and loved."},{"time":235682,"text":"I wanted to be able to create places"},{"time":238170,"text":"that would give you the feeling that you got"},{"time":240135,"text":"in Paley Park,"},{"time":241673,"text":"and not allow developers to\nbuild bleak plazas like this."},{"time":246461,"text":"But over the many years,"},{"time":247876,"text":"I have learned how hard it is"},{"time":250472,"text":"to create successful, meaningful,"},{"time":253060,"text":"enjoyable public spaces."},{"time":255088,"text":"As I learned from my stepfather,"},{"time":256665,"text":"they certainly do not happen by accident,"},{"time":258953,"text":"especially in a city like New York,"},{"time":261781,"text":"where public space has to\nbe fought for to begin with,"},{"time":265060,"text":"and then for them to be successful,"},{"time":267168,"text":"somebody has to think very hard"},{"time":269190,"text":"about every detail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271214,"text":"Now, open spaces in cities are opportunities."},{"time":275160,"text":"Yes, they are opportunities\nfor commercial investment,"},{"time":278964,"text":"but they are also opportunities for the common good"},{"time":282533,"text":"of the city,"},{"time":284299,"text":"and those two goals are often\nnot aligned with one another,"},{"time":287814,"text":"and therein lies the conflict."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290423,"text":"The first opportunity I had to fight"},{"time":293075,"text":"for a great public open space was in the early 1980s,"},{"time":296237,"text":"when I was leading a team of planners"},{"time":298575,"text":"at a gigantic landfill called Battery Park City"},{"time":301887,"text":"in lower Manhattan on the Hudson River."},{"time":304500,"text":"And this sandy wasteland had lain barren"},{"time":307314,"text":"for 10 years,"},{"time":308764,"text":"and we were told, unless we found a developer"},{"time":311408,"text":"in six months, it would go bankrupt."},{"time":313536,"text":"So we came up with a radical,"},{"time":315537,"text":"almost insane idea."},{"time":317927,"text":"Instead of building a park"},{"time":319775,"text":"as a complement to future development,"},{"time":322283,"text":"why don't we reverse that equation"},{"time":324368,"text":"and build a small but very high-quality"},{"time":327421,"text":"public open space first,"},{"time":329406,"text":"and see if that made a difference."},{"time":332412,"text":"So we only could afford to build a two-block section"},{"time":336110,"text":"of what would become a mile-long esplanade,"},{"time":339570,"text":"so whatever we built had to be perfect."},{"time":342537,"text":"So just to make sure, I insisted"},{"time":345533,"text":"that we build a mock-up"},{"time":347750,"text":"in wood, at scale, of the railing and the sea wall."},{"time":351684,"text":"And when I sat down on that test bench"},{"time":354708,"text":"with sand still swirling all around me,"},{"time":357906,"text":"the railing hit exactly at eye level,"},{"time":360999,"text":"blocking my view and ruining my experience"},{"time":363990,"text":"at the water's edge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366120,"text":"So you see, details really do make a difference."},{"time":369427,"text":"But design is not just how something looks,"},{"time":373358,"text":"it's how your body feels on that seat in that space,"},{"time":379250,"text":"and I believe that successful design always depends"},{"time":382390,"text":"on that very individual experience."},{"time":385815,"text":"In this photo, everything looks very finished,"},{"time":390186,"text":"but that granite edge, those lights,"},{"time":392904,"text":"the back on that bench,"},{"time":394792,"text":"the trees in planting,"},{"time":396486,"text":"and the many different kinds of places to sit"},{"time":399089,"text":"were all little battles that turned this project"},{"time":402271,"text":"into a place that people wanted to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406315,"text":"Now, this proved very valuable 20 years later"},{"time":410150,"text":"when Michael Bloomberg asked me to be"},{"time":412158,"text":"his planning commissioner"},{"time":413740,"text":"and put me in charge of shaping"},{"time":415587,"text":"the entire city of New York."},{"time":417658,"text":"And he said to me on that very day,"},{"time":419757,"text":"he said that New York was projected"},{"time":421853,"text":"to grow from eight to nine million people."},{"time":424910,"text":"And he asked me,"},{"time":426440,"text":"\"So where are you going to put"},{"time":428283,"text":"one million additional New Yorkers?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":430999,"text":"Well, I didn't have any idea."},{"time":433644,"text":"Now, you know that New York does"},{"time":436683,"text":"place a high value on attracting immigrants,"},{"time":439381,"text":"so we were excited about the prospect of growth,"},{"time":442301,"text":"but honestly, where were we going to grow"},{"time":445180,"text":"in a city that was already built out to its edges"},{"time":448574,"text":"and surrounded by water?"},{"time":451374,"text":"How were we going to find housing"},{"time":452976,"text":"for that many new New Yorkers?"},{"time":455274,"text":"And if we couldn't spread out,"},{"time":457087,"text":"which was probably a good thing,"},{"time":458901,"text":"where could new housing go?"},{"time":461720,"text":"And what about cars?"},{"time":463353,"text":"Our city couldn't possibly handle any more cars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467465,"text":"So what were we going to do?"},{"time":470299,"text":"If we couldn't spread out, we had to go up."},{"time":474276,"text":"And if we had to go up,"},{"time":475310,"text":"we had to go up in places"},{"time":477092,"text":"where you wouldn't need to own a car."},{"time":479101,"text":"So that meant using one of our greatest assets:"},{"time":481964,"text":"our transit system."},{"time":484416,"text":"But we had never before thought"},{"time":485989,"text":"of how we could make the most of it."},{"time":488225,"text":"So here was the answer to our puzzle."},{"time":491438,"text":"If we were to channel and redirect"},{"time":495069,"text":"all new development around transit,"},{"time":497363,"text":"we could actually handle that population increase,"},{"time":500990,"text":"we thought."},{"time":502264,"text":"And so here was the plan,"},{"time":504822,"text":"what we really needed to do:"},{"time":506470,"text":"We needed to redo our zoning --"},{"time":509318,"text":"and zoning is the city planner's regulatory tool --"},{"time":512669,"text":"and basically reshape the entire city,"},{"time":515980,"text":"targeting where new development could go"},{"time":518125,"text":"and prohibiting any development at all"},{"time":520316,"text":"in our car-oriented,"},{"time":522030,"text":"suburban-style neighborhoods."},{"time":524192,"text":"Well, this was an unbelievably ambitious idea,"},{"time":527924,"text":"ambitious because communities"},{"time":530500,"text":"had to approve those plans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534115,"text":"So how was I going to get this done?"},{"time":537134,"text":"By listening. So I began listening,"},{"time":540042,"text":"in fact, thousands of hours of listening"},{"time":543396,"text":"just to establish trust."},{"time":545214,"text":"You know, communities can tell"},{"time":547303,"text":"whether or not you understand their neighborhoods."},{"time":549455,"text":"It's not something you can just fake."},{"time":552551,"text":"And so I began walking."},{"time":555257,"text":"I can't tell you how many blocks I walked,"},{"time":557577,"text":"in sweltering summers, in freezing winters,"},{"time":560986,"text":"year after year,"},{"time":562816,"text":"just so I could get to understand"},{"time":564904,"text":"the DNA of each neighborhood"},{"time":566931,"text":"and know what each street felt like."},{"time":569506,"text":"I became an incredibly geeky zoning expert,"},{"time":573001,"text":"finding ways that zoning could address"},{"time":575070,"text":"communities' concerns."},{"time":577132,"text":"So little by little, neighborhood by neighborhood,"},{"time":579704,"text":"block by block,"},{"time":581139,"text":"we began to set height limits"},{"time":583012,"text":"so that all new development"},{"time":584744,"text":"would be predictable and near transit."},{"time":588361,"text":"Over the course of 12 years,"},{"time":590142,"text":"we were able to rezone"},{"time":592611,"text":"124 neighborhoods,"},{"time":595180,"text":"40 percent of the city,"},{"time":597959,"text":"12,500 blocks, so that now,"},{"time":602498,"text":"90 percent of all new development of New York"},{"time":605735,"text":"is within a 10-minute walk of a subway."},{"time":608383,"text":"In other words, nobody in those new buildings"},{"time":611033,"text":"needs to own a car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612909,"text":"Well, those rezonings were exhausting"},{"time":617002,"text":"and enervating and important,"},{"time":620040,"text":"but rezoning was never my mission."},{"time":622590,"text":"You can't see zoning and you can't feel zoning."},{"time":626081,"text":"My mission was always to create"},{"time":628169,"text":"great public spaces."},{"time":630093,"text":"So in the areas where we zoned\nfor significant development,"},{"time":633985,"text":"I was determined to create places"},{"time":636176,"text":"that would make a difference in people's lives."},{"time":638870,"text":"Here you see what was"},{"time":640956,"text":"two miles of abandoned, degraded waterfront"},{"time":643380,"text":"in the neighborhoods of Greenpoint"},{"time":645147,"text":"and Williamsburg in Brooklyn,"},{"time":646929,"text":"impossible to get to and impossible to use."},{"time":650489,"text":"Now the zoning here was massive,"},{"time":652983,"text":"so I felt an obligation to create"},{"time":656005,"text":"magnificent parks on these waterfronts,"},{"time":659030,"text":"and I spent an incredible amount of time"},{"time":661770,"text":"on every square inch of these plans."},{"time":664875,"text":"I wanted to make sure that there were"},{"time":666940,"text":"tree-lined paths from the upland to the water,"},{"time":669479,"text":"that there were trees and plantings everywhere,"},{"time":671890,"text":"and, of course, lots and lots of places to sit."},{"time":676078,"text":"Honestly, I had no idea how it would turn out."},{"time":679448,"text":"I had to have faith."},{"time":681073,"text":"But I put everything that I had studied and learned"},{"time":684036,"text":"into those plans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685770,"text":"And then it opened,"},{"time":687430,"text":"and I have to tell you, it was incredible."},{"time":690717,"text":"People came from all over the city"},{"time":692802,"text":"to be in these parks."},{"time":694459,"text":"I know they changed the lives\nof the people who live there,"},{"time":697879,"text":"but they also changed New Yorkers' whole image"},{"time":700374,"text":"of their city."},{"time":702150,"text":"I often come down and watch people"},{"time":703729,"text":"get on this little ferry"},{"time":705245,"text":"that now runs between the boroughs,"},{"time":707223,"text":"and I can't tell you why,"},{"time":708710,"text":"but I'm completely moved"},{"time":710282,"text":"by the fact that people are using it"},{"time":712429,"text":"as if it had always been there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714611,"text":"And here is a new park in lower Manhattan."},{"time":717884,"text":"Now, the water's edge in lower Manhattan"},{"time":720641,"text":"was a complete mess before 9/11."},{"time":723574,"text":"Wall Street was essentially landlocked"},{"time":725489,"text":"because you couldn't get anywhere near this edge."},{"time":728075,"text":"And after 9/11, the city had very little control."},{"time":731909,"text":"But I thought if we went"},{"time":733454,"text":"to the Lower Manhattan Development Corporation"},{"time":735599,"text":"and got money to reclaim this two miles"},{"time":738560,"text":"of degraded waterfront"},{"time":740356,"text":"that it would have an enormous effect"},{"time":742207,"text":"on the rebuilding of lower Manhattan."},{"time":744668,"text":"And it did."},{"time":745848,"text":"Lower Manhattan finally has a public waterfront"},{"time":749239,"text":"on all three sides."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751353,"text":"I really love this park."},{"time":753737,"text":"You know, railings have to be higher now,"},{"time":755962,"text":"so we put bar seating at the edge,"},{"time":758506,"text":"and you can get so close to the water"},{"time":760618,"text":"you're practically on it."},{"time":762346,"text":"And see how the railing widens"},{"time":764215,"text":"and flattens out so you can lay down"},{"time":765631,"text":"your lunch or your laptop."},{"time":767513,"text":"And I love when people come there"},{"time":769493,"text":"and look up and they say,"},{"time":771353,"text":"\"Wow, there's Brooklyn, and it's so close.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":775380,"text":"So what's the trick?"},{"time":777732,"text":"How do you turn a park"},{"time":779541,"text":"into a place that people want to be?"},{"time":782707,"text":"Well, it's up to you,"},{"time":785550,"text":"not as a city planner but as a human being."},{"time":788915,"text":"You don't tap into your design expertise."},{"time":792315,"text":"You tap into your humanity."},{"time":795830,"text":"I mean, would you want to go there?"},{"time":799156,"text":"Would you want to stay there?"},{"time":801139,"text":"Can you see into it and out of it?"},{"time":803277,"text":"Are there other people there?"},{"time":805529,"text":"Does it seem green and friendly?"},{"time":808176,"text":"Can you find your very own seat?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":811414,"text":"Well now, all over New York City,"},{"time":814443,"text":"there are places where you can"},{"time":815947,"text":"find your very own seat."},{"time":817801,"text":"Where there used to be parking spaces,"},{"time":820323,"text":"there are now pop-up cafes."},{"time":822616,"text":"Where Broadway traffic used to run,"},{"time":824594,"text":"there are now tables and chairs."},{"time":826558,"text":"Where 12 years ago, sidewalk\ncafes were not allowed,"},{"time":830112,"text":"they are now everywhere."},{"time":832085,"text":"But claiming these spaces for public use"},{"time":835080,"text":"was not simple,"},{"time":836219,"text":"and it's even harder to keep them that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838881,"text":"So now I'm going to tell you a story"},{"time":840570,"text":"about a very unusual park called the High Line."},{"time":844850,"text":"The High Line was an elevated railway."},{"time":846904,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":853535,"text":"The High Line was an elevated railway"},{"time":855811,"text":"that ran through three neighborhoods"},{"time":857623,"text":"on Manhattan's West Side,"},{"time":859493,"text":"and when the train stopped running,"},{"time":861238,"text":"it became a self-seeded landscape,"},{"time":863394,"text":"a kind of a garden in the sky."},{"time":866001,"text":"And when I saw it the first time,"},{"time":868150,"text":"honestly, when I went up on that old viaduct,"},{"time":870796,"text":"I fell in love the way you fall in love with a person,"},{"time":873612,"text":"honestly."},{"time":874839,"text":"And when I was appointed,"},{"time":876960,"text":"saving the first two sections of the High Line"},{"time":879036,"text":"from demolition became my first priority"},{"time":882408,"text":"and my most important project."},{"time":885080,"text":"I knew if there was a day that I didn't"},{"time":888348,"text":"worry about the High Line, it would come down."},{"time":891951,"text":"And the High Line,"},{"time":893940,"text":"even though it is widely known now"},{"time":896400,"text":"and phenomenally popular,"},{"time":898219,"text":"it is the most contested public space in the city."},{"time":902123,"text":"You might see a beautiful park,"},{"time":904998,"text":"but not everyone does."},{"time":907445,"text":"You know, it's true, commercial interests"},{"time":910082,"text":"will always battle against public space."},{"time":913299,"text":"You might say,"},{"time":915123,"text":"\"How wonderful it is that more than"},{"time":916693,"text":"four million people come from all over the world"},{"time":919124,"text":"to visit the High Line.\""},{"time":920771,"text":"Well, a developer sees just one thing: customers."},{"time":925387,"text":"Hey, why not take out those plantings"},{"time":928112,"text":"and have shops all along the High Line?"},{"time":930120,"text":"Wouldn't that be terrific"},{"time":931617,"text":"and won't it mean a lot more money for the city?"},{"time":934152,"text":"Well no, it would not be terrific."},{"time":936644,"text":"It would be a mall, and not a park."},{"time":939943,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":947322,"text":"And you know what, it might mean"},{"time":948830,"text":"more money for the city,"},{"time":951040,"text":"but a city has to take the long view,"},{"time":955089,"text":"the view for the common good."},{"time":958025,"text":"Most recently, the last section of the High Line,"},{"time":961740,"text":"the third section of the High Line,"},{"time":963356,"text":"the final section of the High Line,"},{"time":964926,"text":"has been pitted against development interests,"},{"time":967728,"text":"where some of the city's leading developers"},{"time":970028,"text":"are building more than 17 million square feet"},{"time":972710,"text":"at the Hudson Yards."},{"time":975010,"text":"And they came to me and proposed"},{"time":976971,"text":"that they \"temporarily disassemble\""},{"time":979530,"text":"that third and final section."},{"time":982260,"text":"Perhaps the High Line didn't fit in"},{"time":984723,"text":"with their image of a gleaming city of skyscrapers"},{"time":987610,"text":"on a hill."},{"time":989073,"text":"Perhaps it was just in their way."},{"time":991797,"text":"But in any case, it took nine months"},{"time":994285,"text":"of nonstop daily negotiation"},{"time":996759,"text":"to finally get the signed agreement"},{"time":998772,"text":"to prohibit its demolition,"},{"time":1000796,"text":"and that was only two years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1004605,"text":"So you see, no matter how popular"},{"time":1007063,"text":"and successful a public space may be,"},{"time":1009899,"text":"it can never be taken for granted."},{"time":1012315,"text":"Public spaces always -- this is it saved --"},{"time":1014896,"text":"public spaces always need vigilant champions,"},{"time":1018608,"text":"not only to claim them at the outset for public use,"},{"time":1022308,"text":"but to design them for the people that use them,"},{"time":1025839,"text":"then to maintain them to ensure"},{"time":1027870,"text":"that they are for everyone,"},{"time":1029840,"text":"that they are not violated, invaded,"},{"time":1032253,"text":"abandoned or ignored."},{"time":1034890,"text":"If there is any one lesson"},{"time":1036534,"text":"that I have learned in my life as a city planner,"},{"time":1039686,"text":"it is that public spaces have power."},{"time":1043446,"text":"It's not just the number of people using them,"},{"time":1046515,"text":"it's the even greater number of people"},{"time":1048469,"text":"who feel better about their city"},{"time":1050588,"text":"just knowing that they are there."},{"time":1053820,"text":"Public space can change how you live in a city,"},{"time":1057292,"text":"how you feel about a city,"},{"time":1059462,"text":"whether you choose one city over another,"},{"time":1062750,"text":"and public space is one of\nthe most important reasons"},{"time":1065521,"text":"why you stay in a city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068642,"text":"I believe that a successful city"},{"time":1071107,"text":"is like a fabulous party."},{"time":1073728,"text":"People stay because they are having a great time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077633,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079576,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1085529,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}